Phase 5b PR5 (docs/plans/phase5-shim-and-task-context.md 決定事項 4) removed
environment.yaml's `workspace_projects` section as part of the environment.yaml
縮退 (buildEnvironmentYAML now emits only allowed_domains + host_commands, the
same reduced WorkspaceEnvView `boid task env` returns). This scenario's hook
discovers the peer's gateway clone URL by grepping
`$HOME/.boid/context/environment.yaml`'s `workspace_projects[].clone_url` line
(see scenario.sh) — that field no longer exists, so the scenario would fail
immediately at the grep step.

Phase 5b PR6 (the "file 配布経路そのものを撤去する目玉 cutover") went further and
retired `$HOME/.boid/context/environment.yaml` — and the rest of the
$HOME/.boid/context/* file family — entirely, so the scenario's hook would now
fail even earlier, at the `[[ -f "$ENV_YAML" ]]` existence check. This does not
change the reason this scenario is skipped (SandboxRuntimeInfo.
WorkspacePeerAdvertise / Runner.buildPeerAdvertise are kept, still computed,
still inert — PR6 made a deliberate call not to wire them anywhere new, per
the same open item below) — it just confirms the file-side workaround this
skip note originally described is no longer available even in principle.

There is currently no CLI/RPC replacement for peer-clone-URL discovery inside
the sandbox (no `GatewayURL`/`GatewayJobToken` env var is threaded through
either — see SandboxRuntimeInfo's own doc comments in sandbox_builder.go).
This is a known, tracked open item in the Phase 5b plan doc (a `boid workspace
peers`-style RPC is deferred to a later 5b item / separate phase, per the plan
doc's PR breakdown item 8 and its "workspace_projects (peer advertise) の CLI
帰属" open question) — not a regression to silently work around here.

Re-enable (drop this file) once that replacement lands and the scenario is
rewritten to use it instead of grepping environment.yaml.
